 applications of the technology that should be practiced. Serving as an introduction to this ethically complicated and significant scientific movement, the book ultimately raises the broader, fundamental question of the meaning of human flourishing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aBioengineering. 0aBioethics. 0aBiotechnologyxReligious aspects. 0aBiotechnologyxSocial aspects. 0aBiotechnology. 0aGenetic engineering. 0aGeneticsxTechnique. 0aHumanities. 0aLife sciences. 0aMedicinexReligious aspects. 0aPhysical sciences. 0aReligion. 0aTechnology. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Science. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Comparative Religion. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Technology. 7aSCIENCE / Biotechnology.2bisacsh1 aArnhart, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBailey, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Ronald M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKass, Leon R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherlock, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilver, Lee M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutton, Sean D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutton, Sean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTirosh-Samuelson, Hava, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842660040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438426600423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781